		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Samsung charger for my Galaxy Note 2 puts out 2A and that still gave a ton of noise with the Super Everdrive. I'm not certain it has anything to do with power draw of the cart, as everything looked great running off of a laptop USB port. I used a similar method to you of just hooking up a snipped USB cable to the charger and running that to the 7805 I and O lines, so I could just unplug from the charger and try it in a bunch of different USB options.<br /><br />It might just come down to the quality of the charger output. After the Kindle charger really let me down (it was my first choice since I never used it) I took a good look at <a href="http://www.righto.com/2012/10/a-dozen-usb-chargers-in-lab-apple-is.html" class="postlink">this page comparing USB chargers with a scope</a> and just decided to bite the bullet and pick up an Apple charger (the Sony one was also good but not mine).

		

		</td>
