	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />They might do that. In the Game Doctor SF3 copier someone noticed that the floppy drive was not getting enough power which was causing read errors and other reliability issues. They fixed this by installing a second regulator that powered just the floppy drive. But you'll need to be sure your external power brick provides enough amperage. That may be a bit tricky for the <span class="posthilit">SNES</span> which has a unique power plug so most power bricks tend to be rated just 850ma. But I suppose you could change the power jack on your <span class="posthilit">SNES</span> console. <br /><br />I wonder if giving DRAM it's very own power regulator would help. But then again, I've never seen this issue.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
